## 8. Personnel Security

People can introduce security risk intentionally or accidentally. Personnel security controls help manage that risk throughout the employment lifecycle.

These controls may include:

* Background screening
* Employment agreements
* Confidentiality agreements
* Acceptable-use requirements
* Security awareness training
* Separation of duties
* Least privilege
* Job rotation
* Mandatory vacations
* Access reviews
* Transfer procedures
* Termination procedures

Access must be updated promptly when an employee changes roles or leaves the organization.

Third-party personnel, contractors, consultants, and vendors should be subject to appropriate security requirements and oversight.

